      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEVEN DAYS (6) progressive filly who returns from a six-month break. Demolished a good field from the wide gate first-up over this track and trip returning excellent figures. Wasn't pushed out in the two trials and the tongue-tie goes on from the good draw. The booking of Tyler Schiller is a good guide to her chances. COSMIC ORDER (4) won her Maiden in determined style at just her second race start over this course and distance. Kept fresh and can keep the winning momentum going. KWIRKY SMILE (10) Ole Kirk filly resuming. Justified the heavy support on debut ($1.60 fav), with a game on-pace victory over 1000m at Nowra six months ago. Primed for this with the two good trial wins at Rosehill. Leading contender who looks set for a good prep. DIFENSIVO (5) big form reversal second-up when he sat on the pace to grip on and finish second over 1000m at Gosford on a heavy (8) surface. Can hold a position from the gate and take a hand in the finish.",
